Now, you want to be sure that they understand what they heard, not because John is not a good teacher, by the way.

23:16.364 --> 23:22.712
But so, it starts coming past you, and it starts going down the Prince of Wales road.

23:22.732 --> 23:23.453
Yeah, I know.

23:24.054 --> 23:24.355
I know.

23:24.375 --> 23:25.176
I know the city will.

23:25.316 --> 23:25.576
I know.

23:25.977 --> 23:28.400
And you start chasing after the limousine.

23:28.420 --> 23:28.981
You're running down.

23:29.001 --> 23:29.281
Hey!

23:29.962 --> 23:30.283
Hey!

23:30.503 --> 23:31.144
Excuse me!

23:31.464 --> 23:32.246
Wait, wait!

23:32.266 --> 23:32.766
Do you know?

23:33.087 --> 23:33.607
Do you know?

23:33.908 --> 23:36.291
Anyway, the limousine, it pulls over.

23:36.952 --> 23:38.354
You pop your head through the window.

23:38.882 --> 23:41.509
You say, do you understand what my pastor was talking about?

23:42.892 --> 23:43.895
They said, no, not really.

23:45.559 --> 23:48.828
Sorry, John, I know you're watching this.

23:48.848 --> 23:49.790
And so he jumps in.

23:50.352 --> 23:52.818
They then start driving around the streets of Norwich.

23:52.994 --> 23:57.440
Half an hour or so later, that man in the limousine says, I want to know Jesus.

23:57.901 --> 23:59.804
They're now on Yarmouth Road.

23:59.824 --> 24:01.166
They see the river, yeah.

24:01.566 --> 24:11.581
They pull the limo over, they get out, they get baptized, he gets baptized, and then he goes on his way, a completely different person.

24:15.867 --> 24:17.810
This is what's going on in the story.

24:18.050 --> 24:21.495
The Bible says he chases the chariot.

24:21.516 --> 24:22.617
He doesn't walk.

24:23.058 --> 24:24.220
He doesn't jog.

24:24.520 --> 24:25.322
He runs.

24:25.943 --> 24:28.306
There is an urgency in his movement.

24:28.647 --> 24:33.515
There is a drive, a determination to put his faith into action.

24:33.795 --> 24:38.963
He is embracing the very thoughts of not knowing what is about to happen next.

24:39.664 --> 24:40.506
Oh, that's risky.

24:41.768 --> 24:42.549
That's risky.

24:43.150 --> 24:45.714
I like to call it brave faith.

24:46.146 --> 24:50.813
You see, Philip doesn't let fear creep in and talk himself out of it.

24:51.073 --> 24:55.921
He's not embarrassed that his actions are a little bit out of the ordinary.

24:56.181 --> 24:58.144
He knows that God has called him.

24:58.465 --> 25:05.295
He knows that he is on a mission and he is gonna run and chase that chariot down until he finishes it.

25:07.718 --> 25:13.627
He either lets that moment pass him by or he grabs a hold of it with both hands.

25:14.429 --> 25:15.410
What a lesson.

25:15.586 --> 25:22.075
to us all, old friend, if ever there was a time to preach the gospel, it is now.

25:22.115 --> 25:27.382
If ever there was a time to stand up for what you believe in, it is now.

25:27.443 --> 25:36.675
If ever there was a time to live on fire for Jesus and go after his mission and the lost people of this world, it is now.

25:36.956 --> 25:38.878
Time is marching on.

25:40.961 --> 25:44.306
And every day chariots will pass you by.

25:44.706 --> 25:54.422
chariots of God opportunities, chariots of divine encounters, chariots of people desperate to hear the good news of Jesus.

25:54.702 --> 25:55.624
Do we see them?

25:55.684 --> 25:57.747
Do we go after them?

25:57.767 --> 26:00.051
Do we chase those chariots?

26:01.013 --> 26:02.014
Or are we too busy?

26:02.816 --> 26:09.266
Are we too busy chasing everything else in this world, the things that are here today and gone tomorrow?

26:09.762 --> 26:19.159
a YouTube busy chasing after fame, a YouTube busy chasing after wealth, a YouTube busy chasing after social media followers.

26:19.639 --> 26:25.650
Perhaps you're too busy chasing after that next high, that next hit or that next bet.

26:26.370 --> 26:30.214
You see, I don't know what you're chasing after, but I do know this.

26:30.574 --> 26:39.263
If it is the things of God, if you're chasing after Him and what He wants you to go after, you will find life, prosperity and honor.

26:39.543 --> 26:43.087
You will discover true value, purpose and meaning.

26:43.367 --> 26:44.969
You will see soul save.

26:45.249 --> 26:47.331
You will see miracles come to pass.

26:47.611 --> 26:50.614
You will leave a legacy with your life.

26:50.634 --> 26:54.418
Oh, if you believe it, give them a hand of praise in this place.

26:59.362 --> 27:04.927
As Benjamin Franklin once said, lost time is never found again.

27:04.987 --> 27:07.170
So spend it wisely.

27:08.030 --> 27:10.313
Spend it on the things that count.

27:10.993 --> 27:14.036
Spend it on things that have eternal value.

27:14.437 --> 27:17.239
Spend it on things that matter to God.

27:17.540 --> 27:20.462
When you step out, others will lean in.

27:20.823 --> 27:25.747
So make sure you chase that chariot, for I promise you, you will not regret it.

27:27.129 --> 27:28.370
You will not regret it.

27:28.802 --> 27:32.648
You know, I woke up at five o'clock this morning, so excited to preach this word.

27:32.688 --> 27:43.385
Thank you for one clap, up there.

27:43.405 --> 27:45.588
I would say that was my mum, but she's on the front row.

27:46.089 --> 27:46.830
It can't be my mum.

27:49.334 --> 27:57.266
The third truth to ignite that courage in you that's going to help you share your faith with others is this.

27:57.570 --> 28:03.999
is that intimidation equals limitation, and perhaps the keys can come forward.

28:05.442 --> 28:07.505
Philip is now in the chariot.

28:09.027 --> 28:23.548
The story goes on to say here in verse 34, that the Ethiopian man asked Philip, tell me, please, who is the prophet talking about himself or someone else?

28:24.510 --> 28:27.474
Then Philip began with that very passage of Scripture.

28:28.002 --> 28:32.086
and told him the good news about Jesus.

28:34.348 --> 28:45.720
When Philip gets into the chariot, probably out of breath and with a sweat on, he wasn't intimidated by who he was now sitting with.

28:47.101 --> 28:56.050
He wasn't concerned or worried about the questions that were about to come his way, for he knew

28:56.290 --> 28:58.133
that he was not there by accident.

28:59.174 --> 29:02.699
He was there by divine appointment.

29:04.622 --> 29:08.928
He had a confidence that bypassed his nerves.

29:10.410 --> 29:24.690
Friend, whenever you step out of your comfort zone to share your faith with someone, there will always be an opportunity for intimidation to step in.

29:27.042 --> 29:37.374
Several years ago, whilst living in East Sussex, I met a guy called Steve at my local gym.

29:38.995 --> 29:44.902
He was an older, rugged, tough-looking, lorry driver.

29:48.726 --> 29:53.432
He heard that I was a pastor, and so he came up to me.

29:53.932 --> 29:55.474
I had never met him before.

29:56.258 --> 30:08.376
I had never had any engagement with this man before, but he bowled up to me and said, don't ever talk to me about Jesus and your church.

30:10.819 --> 30:11.420
I said, okay.

30:13.163 --> 30:13.924
I said, that's fine.

30:15.185 --> 30:17.909
I said, what is your name?

30:17.929 --> 30:19.171
He said, my name's Steve.

30:20.373 --> 30:23.858
I said, Steve, we can talk about something else.

30:24.642 --> 30:28.106
He had a lot of tattoos on his body.

30:28.126 --> 30:30.750
And they asked him if any of them had a meaning.

30:31.871 --> 30:35.556
And he pointed to a big skull that was on his shoulder.

30:36.297 --> 30:40.022
And he said, yeah, this one represents evil.

30:41.664 --> 30:42.485
I said, all right.

30:45.949 --> 30:46.910
I said, did it hurt?

30:48.052 --> 30:51.256
He said, no, the devil looks after his own.

30:52.217 --> 30:52.978
That's what he said.

30:54.530 --> 30:55.711
That's what I was dealing with.

30:57.193 --> 31:00.957
As the weeks passed, we would have a lot of small talk.

31:02.098 --> 31:07.564
We would even train together, but I honored his request.

31:09.467 --> 31:13.091
And then one day, everything changed.

31:14.933 --> 31:23.442
Steve revealed to me that his wife of 30 years had died of cancer seven years earlier.

31:24.578 --> 31:30.507
She had had a faith in God, but in His words, it hadn't done her any good.

31:31.909 --> 31:35.976
He had been drowning in grief ever since.

31:38.139 --> 31:45.470
I said to Steve, I said, Steve, I can't fix your pain, but I can share mine.

31:47.013 --> 31:53.042
I told him about my first daughter, my baby girl called L,

31:54.594 --> 32:06.672
She was a stillborn baby, born at full term, perfectly formed, yet no beating heart, no breath in her lungs.

32:07.974 --> 32:11.219
I never got to see her open her eyes.

32:12.761 --> 32:21.234
Steve, I said it was nine months of development, nine months of dreaming what she was going to look like.

32:22.562 --> 32:24.705
nine months of planning our future.

32:24.725 --> 32:34.518
I said, Steve, it was the most darkest, the most painful chapter of my life.

32:36.300 --> 32:44.310
He then asked me, he said, look, how can you still believe in a God that would allow such tragedy?

32:45.452 --> 32:46.874
And I said, I was honest.

32:47.835 --> 32:50.258
I said, Steve, I don't have all the answers.

32:51.010 --> 32:52.232
I'd been angry too.

32:52.292 --> 33:03.328
In fact, I had questioned my faith on many occasions, but I also told him that it was in that darkness that I found a strength.

33:04.830 --> 33:06.693
I found a strength beyond my own.

33:08.315 --> 33:18.290
I had a deep comfort in knowing that God was with me and a real tangible hope that somehow things would get better.

33:19.170 --> 33:22.893
I said, Steve, I know through my faith.

33:22.914 --> 33:29.179
And I know through my hope in Jesus that I have an assurance that she is in heaven.

33:29.880 --> 33:32.422
And the one day I will hold her again.

33:32.462 --> 33:38.688
And one day I will see her with her eyes wide open.

33:44.674 --> 33:49.138
In that moment, the tough guy and Steve vanish.

33:51.234 --> 33:56.705
We cried, we smiled, we hugged.

33:58.007 --> 34:13.618
The man who strongly warned me to never mention the name Jesus then turned to me and said, what time is your church on a Sunday?

34:20.674 --> 34:26.922
The whole journey with Steve started because I refused to be intimidated.

34:28.984 --> 34:33.630
Intimidation leads to limitation.

34:33.650 --> 34:34.731
In fact, I've learnt this.

34:35.732 --> 34:39.757
Intimidation always gets louder when you listen to it.

34:41.379 --> 34:44.423
There will always be reasons to retreat.

34:45.424 --> 34:48.267
Ah, Luke, I can't share my faith.

34:49.068 --> 34:50.450
I don't have all the answers.

34:51.202 --> 34:52.845
Oh, I don't feel qualified.

34:53.526 --> 34:55.169
I haven't been a Christian very long.

34:55.810 --> 34:56.992
I'm in the minority.

34:57.513 --> 34:58.835
Oh, Luke, you don't understand.

34:58.935 --> 35:02.962
My personality is a little more introverted than yours.

35:03.042 --> 35:05.145
I'll leave that part to someone else.

35:06.207 --> 35:07.890
Oh, church, can I tell you this?

35:08.226 --> 35:38.212
when you're on mission for Jesus Christ and intimidation starts knocking on your door, you need to open that door and answer it with a little bit of faith and say, I may be quieter than others, but I know that I have been fearfully and wonderfully made and I may not feel qualified to speak about God, but I know my God's words are in my mouth and I may be in the minority, but if God be for me, then who can be

35:38.192 --> 36:01.168
against me, I will not fear, for I know the God who made the stars, the God who commanded the oceans, the God who raised the mountains, the God who will supply all your needs, the God who said I will never leave you nor will I forsake you, that God is in you, that God is for you, and that God is on your side.

36:01.528 --> 36:05.234
Oh come on, somebody give him a shout of praise.

36:05.666 --> 36:07.569
Give him a shout of praise.

36:07.589 --> 36:09.091
Give him a shout of praise.

36:16.962 --> 36:17.683
You may take your seats.

36:17.703 --> 36:18.425
I've got one more point.

36:18.445 --> 36:19.606
Look, we're getting ahead of ourselves.

36:21.849 --> 36:27.117
But this is very short, so you'll be back up on your feet in just a moment.

36:27.137 --> 36:33.266
The final key is going to ignite courage in you and help you.

36:34.178 --> 36:41.648
share the gospel and the people in your world is this, is that clear proclamation equals life transformation.

36:43.190 --> 36:47.056
Clear proclamation equals life transformation.

36:48.137 --> 36:56.028
When Philip woke up that morning, he didn't know how he was going to spend the 1,440 minutes.

36:56.649 --> 36:58.331
We all get to spend in a day.

36:59.092 --> 37:03.218
But what he did know was that if he heard the voice of God,

37:03.810 --> 37:08.215
and he stepped out in faith, and he shut the door to intimidation.

37:08.856 --> 37:14.923
Then something big, something powerful, something good was going to happen.

37:16.064 --> 37:16.865
And it did.

37:17.506 --> 37:23.332
The Ethiopian man who he didn't even know about an hour ago has now encountered Jesus.

37:23.993 --> 37:31.922
He has been baptized and goes home to transform a nation, or because Philip knew the good news.

37:32.386 --> 37:33.808
Do you know the good news?

37:34.849 --> 37:36.611
Do you know what the good news is?

37:37.753 --> 37:54.714
If you don't let me tell you, it's found in John 3.16, which says this for God, so love the world, that he gave his one and only son, that whosoever shall believe in him shall not perish, that have eternal life.

37:55.596 --> 37:56.657
That is the good news.

37:57.478 --> 38:00.722
In other words, all our sins from birth to death,

38:01.058 --> 38:03.683
have been paid in full by Jesus Christ.

38:04.244 --> 38:16.166
Christ's death on the cross and resurrection from the grave means that we can all receive forgiveness from our past and you purpose for our today and a brand new hope for our tomorrow.

38:16.486 --> 38:22.738
Know in Jesus as your Lord and Savior means that we can have peace over fear, hope,

38:22.882 --> 38:30.131
over despair, joy, over sorrow, healing, over sickness and victory, over death.

38:30.512 --> 38:34.777
That is the good news.

38:34.797 --> 38:41.145
And there is a world out there that is waiting on you to tell them that.

38:41.165 --> 38:43.668
Oh, we're going to get ready to sing this song again right now.

38:44.870 --> 38:48.815
You see, I know, I know that talking about Jesus isn't easy.

38:49.896 --> 38:51.538
I know that there'll be setbacks.

38:52.002 --> 39:02.153
I know that there'll be disappointments, that there'll be pain, that you will feel uncomfortable, that you will be misunderstood, that you may even feel out of place.

39:02.173 --> 39:06.098
But people need to hear the Word of God.

39:06.118 --> 39:07.820
Time is marching on.

39:08.080 --> 39:09.682
And so today, church, get up.

39:10.202 --> 39:11.544
Come on, let's get up.

39:11.784 --> 39:15.648
The Bible says that today is the day of salvation.

39:15.668 --> 39:16.850
So pick up your cross.

39:17.751 --> 39:19.412
Push into His presence.

39:20.514 --> 39:20.914
Take that step away.

39:22.626 --> 39:37.529
Open up your mouth, open up your mouth, activate your courage.

39:37.549 --> 39:41.796
There is a challenge for you to trust and a vision to complete in the name of Jesus.

39:41.816 --> 39:41.916
Amen.

39:41.936 --> 39:42.036
Amen.

39:42.056 --> 39:42.216
Come on.

39:42.236 --> 39:49.768
Come on, give man a praise if you believe.

39:49.788 --> 39:51.090
He gets all the glory.

39:51.682 --> 39:58.453
All the praise and all the honor for He is a good and faithful God, a God that loves you.

39:59.434 --> 40:01.557
He died on a cross because He loves you.

40:02.198 --> 40:09.370
He rose from the dead because He loves you and you can meet Him in a personal and a powerful way right now.

40:10.111 --> 40:19.986
I always take a moment to give people an opportunity to make their peace with God, to invite Jesus Christ to come alive on the inside of you.

40:20.642 --> 40:22.906
Maybe it's the first time you've come to church.

40:23.406 --> 40:29.876
Perhaps it's the first time you've tuned in online and you don't understand it all, but you know something stirring in your heart.

40:30.557 --> 40:33.622
Or perhaps you need to recommit your life to Christ today.

40:34.183 --> 40:36.306
Maybe your life has got off mission.

40:37.308 --> 40:39.912
But you know you've got to get back on mission.

40:39.932 --> 40:43.257
And that starts by recommitting your life to Jesus.

40:44.158 --> 40:47.243
And so if that's you, I'm going to pray with you in just a moment.

40:47.263 --> 40:49.106
I'm going to count to three and on three.

40:49.186 --> 40:50.647
I want you to slip up your hands.

40:51.588 --> 40:52.429
It's a gift.

40:52.930 --> 40:53.550
It's a gift.

40:53.590 --> 40:54.792
The gift of salvation.

40:55.372 --> 40:56.193
You cannot buy it.

40:56.213 --> 40:57.034
You cannot earn it.

40:57.174 --> 40:58.195
You cannot work for it.

40:58.715 --> 41:00.857
You receive it by saying sorry to God.

41:01.959 --> 41:03.480
I'm repenting of your sins.

41:04.401 --> 41:06.443
And you invite Jesus to come and live in you.

41:07.064 --> 41:11.208
And the Bible says the moment you do that, you become a new creation.

41:11.948 --> 41:13.710
Never to be the same again.

41:14.571 --> 41:17.714
And so right now with heads bowed and eyes closed, no one moving around.

41:18.594 --> 41:22.259
If that's you, just slip up your hands on three.

41:22.339 --> 41:23.481
I see hands going up already.

41:23.501 --> 41:23.922
Here we go.

41:24.082 --> 41:25.083
One, two, three.

41:25.103 --> 41:25.384
That's it.

41:25.424 --> 41:25.904
Lift them up.

41:25.924 --> 41:26.345
Thank you.

41:26.705 --> 41:27.146
Thank you.

41:27.667 --> 41:28.488
Thank you at the back.

41:28.528 --> 41:29.309
Wonderful.

41:29.329 --> 41:30.150
Thank you in the middle.

41:30.170 --> 41:30.851
Wonderful.

41:30.871 --> 41:31.692
Thank you down here.

41:31.712 --> 41:32.794
That's wonderful.

41:32.814 --> 41:34.637
Anyone else join these people?

41:34.657 --> 41:35.458
Thank you.

41:35.478 --> 41:36.259
Thank you.

41:36.279 --> 41:37.401
That's wonderful.

41:37.421 --> 41:37.901
Anyone else?

41:37.941 --> 41:38.802
Thank you right up there.

41:38.823 --> 41:41.026
I see your hands too.

41:41.046 --> 41:41.526
Praise God.

41:41.566 --> 41:42.648
You can put your hands down.

41:43.549 --> 41:46.994
As I said, I'm going to lead you through a simple prayer of faith.

41:47.618 --> 41:50.442
and we're gonna all pray together as a church family.

41:51.142 --> 41:53.946
And so come on church, repeat these words after me.

41:54.527 --> 41:55.107
Let's pray.

41:56.209 --> 42:04.219
Dear Lord Jesus, thank you for dying for me to forgive all my sins and failures.

42:06.462 --> 42:12.349
I believe that you rose from the dead so that I can have a brand new life.

42:14.512 --> 42:16.114
Please come into my heart

42:17.410 --> 42:26.963
and help me by the power of the Holy Spirit to trust and live for you in Jesus name.

42:28.305 --> 42:28.746
Amen.

42:29.507 --> 42:30.108
And amen.

42:30.208 --> 42:37.197
Come on, let's give those people and our God around the globe.

42:37.217 --> 42:39.801
Wonderful.

42:39.821 --> 42:46.290
Pastor Matt is going to get up in a minute and tell those people what to do next, but I want to be the first to congratulate you.

42:46.946 --> 42:50.010
I made that commitment to Christ at 20 years old.

42:50.951 --> 42:52.693
I'm 41 now.

42:52.713 --> 42:53.694
I know I don't look it.

42:54.796 --> 42:55.717
God's been good to me.

42:56.918 --> 42:58.740
And I believe he's gonna be good to you too.

42:59.321 --> 43:00.783
The best decision you'll ever make.

43:01.604 --> 43:03.326
But before I finish, I wanna pray for you.

43:04.648 --> 43:07.811
I believe I carry the spirit of an evangelist.

43:08.933 --> 43:12.437
That there is faith in me and I wanna impart some of my faith into you.

43:13.418 --> 43:16.562
That you leave this place today with a new courage.

43:17.186 --> 43:20.451
that you're gonna chase those chariots that pass you down.

43:20.511 --> 43:27.080
I guarantee you that even today for some of you chariots are gonna pass you by to tell people about Jesus.

43:27.961 --> 43:30.905
And we're once upon a time you would have taken a step back.

43:31.546 --> 43:33.549
You would have let that chariot pass you by.

43:34.350 --> 43:35.572
Today you're gonna run after it.

43:36.413 --> 43:39.458
As if you're running after that limousine down the Prince of Wales road.

43:40.679 --> 43:43.063
So grab the hand of the person on your left and on your right.

43:44.304 --> 43:45.426
We're in it together.

43:46.530 --> 43:48.193
We're on mission together.

43:49.474 --> 43:54.843
We're gonna see this city and your world want to Jesus together.

43:54.863 --> 43:57.406
And so let me pray over you right now.

43:58.288 --> 44:04.497
Dear God, I thank you for every man, woman and child in this room and watching online.

44:05.238 --> 44:07.081
Lord, I thank you for their faithfulness.

44:07.822 --> 44:13.390
I thank you for their courage, but today I ask that you would impart into them a new boldness.

44:14.332 --> 44:15.794
Lord, that they will take

44:15.938 --> 44:36.180
take the moments that come their way with both hands, that you would give them the words to say, that there will be a fire in their bones, that there will be a fire in their mouths, that as they speak your word will come forth and penetrate the lives of those that are broken, those that are lost, those that are hurting.

44:36.941 --> 44:38.463
We will not be intimidated.

44:39.424 --> 44:44.850
Lord, we will rise up and we will see this city, this nation,

44:45.058 --> 44:53.570
And the people of this world want to you in the mighty, powerful and awesome name of Jesus.

44:53.590 --> 44:56.514
And everybody say amen.

44:57.235 --> 44:57.996
Amen.

44:59.078 --> 45:05.387
Go ahead.

45:05.407 --> 45:06.308
Come on one more time.

45:06.328 --> 45:10.514
Let's thank Luke for extraordinary words.

45:13.922 --> 45:16.124
Giving us courage to go out on mission today.

45:16.164 --> 45:17.906
Thank you, Lou.

45:17.946 --> 45:21.811
For everybody that made that decision, one amazing moment that was in the service.

45:21.851 --> 45:28.859
And we want to honour that moment, that decision that you've made today, saying yes to Jesus, beginning your faith journey, following Him.

45:28.879 --> 45:36.327
And I know we've got team Ben and Patricia down here and we've got a little room, our chapel, it's just designed to connect with you after the service.

45:36.367 --> 45:39.250
Now, it's a great chance for you to use a bit of courage.

45:39.522 --> 45:46.957
that you've received from that message and come straight down to Ben and Patricia, we'd love to give to you a John's gospel about the life, the account of Jesus.

45:47.478 --> 45:50.363
Help you on your way, encourage you to go and live for him.

45:50.384 --> 45:54.091
And so, come on, can we celebrate with everybody who's made that decision again today?

45:54.131 --> 46:01.746
Praise God, it's brilliant.

46:01.922 --> 46:09.752
If you said yes to Jesus today by saying the Salvation Prayer, we'd love for you to email connections at soulchurch.com.

46:10.052 --> 46:14.618
So we can talk to you a little bit more about this incredible decision you've just made.

46:15.259 --> 46:23.709
And if at any point in the service, you felt moved to give towards any of our local or global initiatives, head to soulchurch.com.

46:23.729 --> 46:30.738
And don't forget to stay connected with us on Facebook, Instagram, and YouTube by searching at Soul Church UK.

46:31.042 --> 46:32.594
Take care and God bless.

